    "Fernandez-Quilez et al. [147] observed that pretraining with SimCLR [23] improved downstream segmentation performance, compared random and ImageNet-pretrained initialization.",
    "Wang et al. [148] engineered a more complex pretext task for the same downstream task, which involved optimizing a contrastive learning objective where images from the same patient comprise a positive pair, and an augmentation classification objective.",
    "Bolous et al. [149] also observed an improvement for the same downstream task with a private dataset when pretraining using a reconstructive pretext task."
